text.tspan: Geothermal Energy Storage
Thermal energy (heat) is stored underground
below Vandkulturhuset, within 14 boreholes
drilled to a depth of 250 meters.
Solar Power
A solar energy grid powers the heat
pumps with renewable electricity.
Fan Coils
Fan coils circulate warm and cool air
from the heat pump system into our
pools and community room.
Outdoor Pool
The outdoor pool is warmed with heat
stored underground, as well as heat pulled
from the community room and ice baths.
Ice Baths
Like the community room but a lot colder!
Ice baths are chilled by removing heat and
transferring it into the underground system
or outdoor pool.
Community Room
Heat is drawn away from the community
room, cooling it in the process. This heat is
either stored underground or used to warm
the outdoor pool.
Energy Machines Control
The brain of the system. Smart controls keep the
geothermal energy cycle in balance and running eff
ciently storing energy when its not needed, using
it when it is, and ensuring energy is never wasted.
Energy Machines Heat Pumps
Two electric-powered heat pumps create
heating and cooling by moving heat
between the boreholes and building.
